-- Pimco posts $5.5 bln in net outflows from U.S. mutual funds in May - Morningstar
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 10:57AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 3 (Reuters) - Bond giant Pimco posted $5.5 billion in net outflows across its U.S. open-end mutual funds in May, extending the firm's record outflow streak to 12 straight months, Morningstar data showed on Tuesday.

